    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "It's a bit a strange issue, but sometimes the things are broken, the module is either simply not compiled, or it is compiled, but crashes the interpreter. In some cases I do not care about performance much, but I want the things just work. It's better to have a tool working slowly than non-working at all.\n\nSo it'd be nice to have a knob to make it generate just python code instead of compilation the c++ one.",
    "closed_at": "2018-01-12T19:43:50Z",
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "OWNER",
            "body": "Could you clarify? You want to generate Python code from a Cython .pyx code file, right?\n\nNote that this can only work with code that does not use any actual C or C++ functionality, i.e. this would be a fairly limited feature.\n\nIt's also not clear to me what the concrete use case is. Do you consider this a pure debugging feature, or does it go beyond that? A more concrete motivation would help to understand this request better.\n",
